<div class="container my-4">
  <h1>Incomplete Addresses</h1>
  <p class="text-muted">
    Active subscriptions whose address wasn't picked from the Mapbox finder, so it's
    missing the suburb/postcode/province a driver needs. Rows in red don't even
    mention their assigned suburb in the address text — check the suburb field itself
    before just filling in the rest of the address.
  </p>

  <p><strong><%= @subscriptions.count %></strong> of active subscriptions need a look.</p>

  <table class="table table-sm align-middle">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>ID</th>
        <th>Customer</th>
        <th>Suburb</th>
        <th>Current Address</th>
        <th></th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% @subscriptions.each do |sub| %>
        <tr class="<%= 'table-danger' if sub.suburb_missing_from_address? %>">
          <td>#<%= sub.id %></td>
          <td>
            <%= sub.user&.full_name %><br>
            <span class="text-muted small"><%= sub.user&.email %></span>
          </td>
          <td><%= sub.suburb %></td>
          <td><%= sub.street_address %></td>
          <td><%= link_to "Edit", edit_subscription_path(sub), class: "btn btn-sm btn-primary", target: "_blank" %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
